         <abstract id="aspace_b1a7c93211c9a4cab3862dfb7a69a09e">This collection contains leather bookplates, including both standard bookplates as well as supralibros, or super ex-libris, which are marks of ownership typically stamped on the exterior cover of a book.</abstract>
    
      </did>
      <acqinfo id="aspace_0598592325e410b2017281bae8e1f375">
         <head>Immediate Source of Acquisition</head>
         <p>The Yale Bookplate Collection was formerly housed in Sterling Memorial Library. The collection was incorporated into the Arts of the Book Collection in 1984 and then moved to the Seeley G. Mudd Library in 1990. In 2011, it was transferred to the Robert B. Haas Family Arts Library.</p>  
      </acqinfo>
      <accessrestrict id="aspace_f2360feda029924ec78e45360b0f7961">
